// ward-kdl pkg brew - the brew passthrough surface as an allowlist (cli-guard
// execverb, exec dialect). Re-expresses the read/passthrough half of ward's
// hand-rolled `ward pkg brew` wrapper (cmd/ward/pkg_brew.go) as a guardfile,
// per the coily -> ward -> ward-kdl consolidation (ward#94, epic ward#91).
//
// The binary is fixed at parse, so the caller can never substitute it, and
// every verb runs under cli-guard's sandbox jail: ward is bind-mounted over
// `brew` inside the jail, so a grandchild that re-invokes brew re-enters the
// gate rather than escaping it. That jail / grandchild enforcement is the
// property this re-expression preserves - it rides the exec dialect, not the
// retired Go.
//
// Deny-by-default. Only the read-only and pure-passthrough verbs mount here:
// the inspection reads, `brew update`, and `brew bundle` (which the Go wrapper
// forwards verbatim). The scoped mutating verbs - formula-scoped install/
// uninstall/upgrade/reinstall/link/unlink/pin/unpin, tap-scoped tap/untap, and
// the touch-everything cleanup/autoremove - carry the primary-org tap scope and
// the `--allow-untapped` opt-out.
//
// ward#95 decided that scope policy does NOT fit the exec dialect and is not
// reachable as a complex action from ward at cli-guard v0.43.0: the `when` /
// `deny-when` guards are existential (∃ one match) where the rule is universal
// (∀ formula in-scope), have no conditional escape hatch for `--allow-untapped`,
// can't strip that ward-side flag before forwarding to brew, can't deny a bare
// zero-positional `upgrade`, and the gate registry is closed (only `aws-read`,
// no `Config.Gates` seam). So the scoped half stays as hand-written gated Go
// (cmd/ward/pkg_brew.go) - mirroring ward#92's forgejo_issue.go outcome - until
// cli-guard grows a custom-gate seam. They are listed as `never run` here to
// mark the boundary; an unlisted verb is denied either way.
// Full rationale: ../../docs/ward-kdl.brew.scoped.md.
wrap ward-kdl pkg brew {
    exec brew
    // reads - inspection verbs, nothing mutated
    can run search {
        describe "search formulae/casks by name or regex"
    }
    can run info {
        describe "show formula/cask metadata; pass the name"
    }
    can run list {
        describe "list installed formulae/casks"
    }
    can run deps {
        describe "show a formula's dependency tree"
    }
    can run leaves {
        describe "list installed formulae not depended on"
    }
    can run outdated {
        describe "list formulae with a newer version available"
    }
    can run doctor {
        describe "diagnose common brew problems"
    }
    can run config {
        describe "print brew's configuration"
    }
    can run commands {
        describe "list available brew commands"
    }
    can run "services list" {
        describe "list managed services and their state"
    }
    can run "services info" {
        describe "detail a managed service; pass the name"
    }
    // passthrough - mutates brew's own state, not the install graph; the Go
    // wrapper forwards these verbatim, so they pass through here too
    can run update {
        describe "refresh formulae definitions from the taps"
    }
    can run bundle {
        describe "install from a Brewfile; pass --file to point at one"
    }
    // scoped mutating verbs - primary-org tap scope + --allow-untapped, kept as
    // gated Go in cmd/ward/pkg_brew.go (ward#95 decision); denied here
    never run install
    never run uninstall
    never run upgrade
    never run reinstall
    never run link
    never run unlink
    never run pin
    never run unpin
    never run tap
    never run untap
    never run cleanup
    never run autoremove
}
